{
  "texts": [
    "The five bins for consolidation are presented as 5.553 (95% CI: 4.727 to 6.387), 6.230 (95% CI: 5.826 to 6.604), 7.219 (95% CI: 6.447 to 8.093), 9.631 (95% CI: 7.575 to 11.707) and 11.915 (95% CI: 9.683 to 14.186).",
    "The five bins for edema are presented as 7.761 (95% CI: 7.127 to 8.419), 12.777 (95% CI: 11.909 to 13.616), 18.254 (95% CI: 16.937 to 19.523), 19.268 (95% CI: 16.246 to 22.671) and 39.059 (95% CI: 27.886 to 49.837).",
    "The four bins for lesion are presented as 3.185 (95% CI: 2.973 to 3.386), 4.507 (95% CI: 3.856 to 5.170), 2.738 (95% CI: 1.476 to 4.203) and 22.835 (95% CI: 13.974 to 32.555).",
    "The five bins for pleural effusion are presented as 3.404 (95% CI: 2.794 to 4.077), 3.473 (95% CI: 2.950 to 4.013), 4.401 (95% CI: 3.644 to 5.173), 5.940 (95% CI: 4.794 to 7.119) and 6.073 (95% CI: 4.431 to 7.915).",
    "The five bins for pleural other are presented as 0.410 (95% CI: 0.348 to 0.473), 0.729 (95% CI: 0.529 to 0.938), 1.202 (95% CI: 0.626 to 2.120), 1.668 (95% CI: 0.549 to 3.153) and 6.883 (95% CI: 3.940 to 10.317)."
